      "payload": {
        "tool": "task",
        "args": {
          "description": "Write protocol.yaml week 4 update",
          "prompt": "You are the planner sub-agent. Write ONLY under protocols/.\n\n## Aggregate inputs\n\n**Evaluator:** classification = progress. HRV trend +9ms (32\u219241) clears progressing exactly ONE exercise this cycle; recovery 82, sleep 78; no hold/regress triggers; no exercise-specific pain. All other exercises must stay at current week-3 prescription.\n\n**Researcher:** From protocols/protocol-library/post-acl-week-4.yaml lines 28-33: terminal_knee_extension should be sets 3, reps 15, load green_band, ROM_target_deg 0. From post-acl-week-4.yaml lines 41-44: stationary_bike would be duration 15, RPE 5 \u2014 but we must NOT apply bike progression because only one exercise advances (evaluator). quad_sets and heel_slides have no week-4 blocks in library; keep current protocol.yaml values for them unchanged.\n\n## Current protocols/protocol.yaml (week 3)\n- patient Andre, phase post-ACL reconstruction\n- Exercises: quad_sets (3x15, bw, ROM 90), heel_slides (3x10, bw, ROM 100), terminal_knee_extension (3x12 yellow_band, ROM 0), stationary_bike (10 min RPE 4)\n- Each exercise needs progression_criteria, regression_criteria, references[] per schema\n\n## Required output\n1. Update protocols/protocol.yaml:\n   - week: 4\n   - generated_by: planner (or cloud-planner)\n   - last_updated: 2026-05-02\n   - session_targets: unchanged from current\n   - Progress ONLY terminal_knee_extension: reps 15, load green_band; update progression_criteria/regression_criteria if needed to stay clinically sensible; references MUST include protocol-library/post-acl-week-4.yaml (and keep prior reference pattern)\n   - quad_sets, heel_slides, stationary_bike: identical numerics and criteria to current file except update any references that should cite week-3 library still where appropriate\n2. protocols/schedule.yaml: Create ONLY if the protocol convention needs it for week 4. If not needed for a minimal weekly update, do not create schedule.yaml.\n\nValidate mentally against protocols/schema.json and protocols/.cursorrules (don't decrease ROM without symptoms; cite library; minimal diff).\n\nMake the edits to the repo files directly. Then summarize what you changed.",
          "subagentType": {
            "custom": {
              "name": "planner"
            }
          },
          "model": "composer-2-fast"
        }
      }
